results.headline: Fight Club (Movie)
results.summary_short: The sardonic, testosterone-fueled science fiction of this grunge parable means to hit raw nerves. Making a tougher but less stomach-turning film than his earlier "Seven," David Fincher taps into the nexus of computer-age malevolent fantasy and attempts to psychoanalyze an entire culture in ways that aren't entirely clear until the film's whammy of a denouement arrives. A reckless but fascinating attempt, expertly acted, to make sense of contemporary frustrations. â€” Janet Maslin
